From: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] test excludes include cstdint

Fixes compile failure in shared test helper where uint32_t is used
without including <cstdint>.

Upstream already added this include on master; backported here for the
pinned releases/25.48 branch:
  d682c49ef1c9782873ed3c7684e6a07180531b48
  ("test: add more missing headers for GCC 15")

Upstream-Status: Backport [https://github.com/intel/compute-runtime/commit/d682c49ef1c9782873ed3c7684e6a07180531b48]

Signed-off-by: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
---
 .../shared/test/common/test_macros/test_excludes.cpp        | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

Index: intel-compute-runtime-25.48.36300.8/shared/test/common/test_macros/test_excludes.cpp
===================================================================
--- intel-compute-runtime-25.48.36300.8.orig/shared/test/common/test_macros/test_excludes.cpp
+++ intel-compute-runtime-25.48.36300.8/shared/test/common/test_macros/test_excludes.cpp
@@ -12,6 +12,7 @@
 #include <map>
 #include <memory>
 #include <string>
+#include <cstdint>
 #include <unordered_set>
 
 using namespace NEO;
